title.romaji: Youkai Watch Jam: Youkai Gakuen Y - N to no Souguu

description:
The super elite school Y Academy is shrouded in many mysteries. The ‘YSP Club’ tackles those very mysteries. And not just that, they can also transform into 'Yo-kai Heroes’. They are entrusted with the mission of solving the greatest mysteries in Yo-kai history. An overly powerful student council, a ruthless disciplinary committee, and even an alien invasion.

What awaits Jinpei, and the other 'YSP Club’ members? A bright future? Or perhaps...Sudden gag overload. Touching developments that’ll move you to tears. A completely new experience is waiting for you. Unravel the biggest mystery of the Y Academy...no, the entire world.

(Source: Yokai Watch Wiki)
synonyms: Yo-kai Gakuen Y: Encounter With N

node.description:
__[Website](https://strawberryprince.com/) | [Twitter](https://twitter.com/StPri_info) | [YouTube](https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCdB5vhQORw9HeiF82IYLnjw)__

__Introduction:__
Strawberry Prince, alternatively known as StPri, is a Japanese 6-member entertainment group and unit consisting of various utaite. 

__Biography:__
The current members are noted to be particularly close, as shown by a large number of collab covers. Besides singing they also post various small skits, collaborate and solo, to their individual channels.

Although it isn't officially confirmed, they have a pattern with their covers suggesting duets to be their forté, an example is their duet "[Dance of Venus](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ICuLhf1OckI&feature=youtu.be)", where you can experience how well they harmonize with one another.

__Members:__
- [Nanamori](https://anilist.co/staff/202769/Nanamori) (ななもり) – vocalist
- [Root](https://anilist.co/staff/181478/Root) (るぅと) – vocalist, also does composition
- [Colon](https://anilist.co/staff/202768/Colon) (ころん) – vocalist
- [Satomi](https://anilist.co/staff/198949/Satomi) (さとみ) – vocalist
- [Rinu](https://anilist.co/staff/148136/Rinu) (莉犬) – vocalist
- [Jel](https://anilist.co/staff/202767/Jel) (ジェル) – vocalist

__Former Members:__
- [Kanna](https://twitter.com/kanna0kyun) (かんな) – vocalist
- [Shiyun](https://twitter.com/shiyun_2525) (しゆん) – vocalist
- [Ketchup](https://twitter.com/ketchup_N1) (けちゃっぷ) – vocalist
- [Yuuku](https://twitter.com/yuuku_2525) (ゆうく) – vocalist

[Website](https://96neko.jp/) | [Twitter (Main)](https://twitter.com/96__neko) | [Twitter (Sub)](https://twitter.com/96_neko_sub) | [YouTube 1](https://www.youtube.com/user/96nekoch) | [YouTube 2](https://www.youtube.com/c/SUB-96NEKOCHANNEL) | [Nico Nico Douga](https://www.nicovideo.jp/user/9217369/mylist/15614906) | [Bilibili](https://space.bilibili.com/392617988) | [OPENREC](https://www.openrec.tv/user/96nyan)

__Introduction:__
96Neko, pronounced as Kuroneko, is an utaite and has been active in the vocaloid scene since 2009. She has covered over 200 songs in addition to performing, writing, composing and producing a large amount of original songs of her own.

She is well-known for her husky, low range vocals and for being a "ryouseirui", a term used to describe vocalists who are able to sing in both typical male and female vocal ranges. However, she is also able to sing in a very cute female voice, which can be heard in her cover of [Soratobazu](https://www.nicovideo.jp/watch/sm19159618).

96Neko is also a Virtual YouTuber and posts her activities on her sub-channel. On October 5, 2019, she had announced her new VTuber persona by the name of Kuroki Natsume. As of July 9, 2021, she settled to merge the personas, expressing that she finds it limiting (and other factors) and decided to perform all her activities under her utaite name. However, she stated that people may still call her VTuber persona by whatever name they want, whether it be Kuroki Natsume or Kuroneko, and asked them to not worry.

__Biography:__
During her early utaite career on Nico Nico Douga, she would often do duets with the vocaloids [Kagamine Rin](https://anilist.co/staff/191794/Rin-Kagamine) and [Kagamine Len](https://anilist.co/staff/154290/Len-Kagamine). She also sung many parody songs, where she mostly dueted with Kagamine Len or [vipTenchou](https://twitter.com/viptentyo). In later years, she would start collaborating with the utaite [Amatsuki](https://anilist.co/staff/131102/Amatsuki) in duets.

96Neko requested that people shouldn't record her anonymously with the intention of redistributing the footage commercially. She is fine with people recording for personal entertainment usage, however.

Her album, Iris, which was released just three days before her twentieth birthday, was her way of thanking her fans and supporters prior to her turning twenty. It also served as a final installment to her teenage years as an utaite.

Alfakyun. (あるふぁきゅん。) is a utaite who started in June 2013. Despite this, her most popular cover, "Guren no Yumiya" has already gained 3.1 million views as of July 2016, doing so in only a few months.

She can switch between both low and high voices with ease, which especially can be seen on her covers of "E? Aa, Sou." and "How-to Sekai Seifuku" and notably in her newest album rootage/α. that was released on 2018/08/15.

Her low voice is known to be unusually very powerful for a woman, while her high voice is very feminine and cute such as demonstrated in her cover of "Chototsu Moushin Girl" and notably in her newest album rootage/α. that was released on 2018/08/15

Japanese: あるふぁきゅん。 (arufuakyun.)
Also known as: +α/Alfakyun.＋α/Alphakyun.

[Youtube](https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCnVDCsEQf-sl6X2ttbqlDHA) | [Twitter](https://twitter.com/alfa10alfa) | [Webiste](http://alfakyun.com/) | [nicovideo profile](http://www.nicovideo.jp/user/2834277) | [nicovideo mylist](http://www.nicovideo.jp/mylist/37540797) | [nicovideo community](http://com.nicovideo.jp/community/co2047182)
